response.value:
To add a gap between the app icon and the app name in wofi, you can target the text element inside each entry. Usually, the icon and text are in separate elements, so you can use a left margin on the text or a right margin on the icon.

Try adding this to your CSS:

```css
#entry image {
  margin-right: 10px;
}

#entry #text {
  margin-left: 10px;
}
```

This will add space between the icon and the app name. Adjust the pixel value as needed for your preference. Let me know if you want me to add this directly!

